condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Loan Agreement, Schedule 2, Section I. A. 3. | Description :The Borrower shall on a date to be agreed with theBank, but in no case later than twenty-four (24) months after the Effective Date, carry out a review with the Bank on the overallprogress and implementation arrangements in the execution of the Project and set out the measures and take any remedial action as aresult of such review, as agreed with the Bank. | Due Date :30-Sep-2017

New Definition of Transfer Agreement included: "Transfer Agreement” means Convenio modificatorio al contrato de concesion, theagreement referred to in Section I.A.4 of Schedule 2 of this Agreement, that establishes the conditions under which Interagua shallbe remunerated for the operation and maintenance of the infrastructure developed under the project.

title.narrative: Share of poor people in urban areas provided with access to improved sanitation services under the project

Volume(mass) of BOD pollution load removed by treatment plant under the project
Reduction of the annually reported repair tickets in the La Chala sector sewer main system
Share of surveyed beneficiaries (gender disaggregated) that feel project investments reflect their needs
People in urban areas provided with access to improved sanitation services under the project
Meters of sewers mains rehabilitated under the project
Citizen Engagement: Number of beneficiary households that sign a certification that they are satisfied with the works conducted in their houses.
New household sewer connections constructed under the project
Water Quality Monitoring System for the Estero Salado Estuary
Water quality Monitoring System for the Daule and Guayas River finalized and system operational
Start of Construction of Las Esclusas WWTP
Share of the monthly average effluent from Los Merinos WWTP outlet discharged into the Daule River is compliant with regulatory quality standard for BDO, TSS and total coliforms
Start of Construction of Los Merinos WWTP
Percentage of Component 1 social mobilization team members that are women
The Los Merinos WWTP Forest Compensation Plan has being developed and approved by National Environmental Authorities
